    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/561</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-12T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1024. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 1217. Department’s 687, your 1012, August 9, 9 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>]
                    p.m. We assume ship is <hi rend="italic">Helios</hi>. It will only be necessary
                    to issue United <pb facs="0157" n="991" xml:id="pg_991"/> States export license
                    covering cargo, as Contraband Committee has cabled British Consul, Buenos Aires,
                        <hi rend="italic">re</hi> the lots approved and Consul will have certified
                    manifest. Swedish Legation informed of numbers through mistake. In future cases
                    export applications for shipment from Buenos Aires, Santos, Montevideo, Rio de
                    Janeiro, Bahia, for Sweden will be submitted to Contraband Committee through
                    newly established Swedish trade office in London. The Contraband Committee’s
                    approval will be cabled to British consul at port of shipment, who will certify
                    to correctness of manifest. I suggest that similar certificates might be
                    required from American consuls.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
